I don't exactly fully understand your coding (nothing on your part, I'm just a noob, so I'm having a bit of trouble following along with your item iteration layers, I haven't really learned this aspect of coding yet very well), nor do I still exactly understand what you're trying to achieve or in how you want to achieve it, but it seems like you're tackling your goals in the wrong way or method.

the &quot;display amount&quot; [Red_Apples (99), Green_Apples (99), etc) and the objects themselves, are two separate entities, so I think you're over complicated it in this regard. Move your objects to a storage object, and also then just adjust your display amounts (see my code below, I think I've got the right~good ideas on doing this). Or do it however you want, but work with each (the objects and the display amounts) separately, and then just connect them (e.i. = whatever you do with your objects, then simply have the display amount adjust to it).

------------

